				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\rm{\Delta }}{\omega }_{max}\propto {\rm{\Delta }}{T}_{f}^{-1}$$\end{document}. Thus we can obtain an estimate of the required maximum nonlinear phase shift, i.e. the maximum B-integral, for any given initial and final (compressed) pulse durations:1Bmax=ΔTi0.86ΔTf.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
